natspec.details: Implementation of ERC-1155 non-fungible token standard ownable, with approval, OPENSEA compatible (name, symbol)

params.name: the smart contract name
params.uri: the new uri for the contract

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: Can also be used to check ownership of an ID

params.accounts: a dynamic array of the addresses to check the balance for
params.ids: a dynamic array of the token IDs to check the balance

burn(uint256,uint256).details: the amount of tokens will be deducted from the holder's balance

params.amount: of tokens to burnfor this ID
params.id: the ID of the token to burn

burnBatch(uint256[],uint256[]).details: inside the loop ownership will be checked for each token. We can not burn tokens we do not own

params.amounts: array of amounts of tokens for each ID in the ids array
params.ids: array of ids for the tokens to burn

mint(address,uint256,uint256,bytes32).details: this can be a new token or "topping up" the balance of a non-fungible token ID

params.data: the data associated with this mint. Usually stays empty
params.receiver: the account that will receive the minted token

mintBatch(address,uint256[],uint256[],by.details: this can be new tokens or "topping up" the balance of existing non-fungible token IDs in the contract

params.amounts: amounts of tokens for each ID in the ids array
params.data: the data associated with this mint. Usually stays empty
params.ids: array of ids for the tokens
params.receiver: the account that will receive the minted token

pause().details: not part of the core spec but a common feature for NFT projects

renounceOwnership().details: emits an OwnershipTransferred event with the old and new zero owner addresses

safeBatchTransferFrom(address,address,ui.details: transfer tokens from one address to another.

params.amounts: a dynamic array of the amounts for the specified list of ids.
params.ids: a dynamic array of the token ids that will be sent

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: transfer token from one address to another.

params.amount: the amount of tokens for the specified id
params.id: the token id that will be sent

setApprovalForAll(address,address,bool).details: set an operator for a certain NFT owner address

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns True if the interface is supported

params.newOwner: The address of the new owner.
